---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 139
By: Eckhart
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Detachment From Place and
    Conditions
---
To whom God is dearer in one thing than another, that man is a barbarian,
still in the wilds, a child. He to whom God is the same in everything has
come to man's estate. But he to whom creatures all mean want and exile has
come into his own.
